
.TH MUHHWM 1 muhhwm\-VERSION
.SH NAME
muhhwm \- a tiling window manager for X
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B muhhwm
.SH DESCRIPTION
muhhwm is a tiling window manager for X11. Windows are organised into
tags and namespaces. Each namespace has its own set of six tags, and
only one namespace is active at a time. This lets you keep separate
contexts (such as study, code, and free time) without them interfering
with each other.
.P
Three layouts are available: tiled, monocle, and floating. In tiled
mode the screen is split into a master area on the left and a stack on
the right. The proportion of the screen given to the master area is
configurable. Monocle shows one window at a time maximised to the full
bar-adjusted screen area. Floating imposes no layout and windows can
be moved and resized freely.
.P
The bar appears at the top of the screen and shows the current
namespace, the tag strip, and the title of the focused window.
muhhbar is a separate status bar process and is not managed by
muhhwm directly.
.SH NAMESPACES
muhhwm has three namespaces: study, code, and free. Each namespace
maintains its own tag state independently. Switching namespaces
preserves the tag selection in the namespace you are leaving and
restores it when you return.
.SH TAGS
Each namespace has six tags numbered 1 through 6. A window can belong
to one or more tags. Only windows that belong to the currently selected
tag or tags are shown on screen.
.SH CONFIGURATION
muhhwm is configured by editing
.B config.h
and recompiling. There is no runtime configuration file.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
The modifier key is Super (the Windows key), written as Mod below.
.SS Windows
.TP
.B Mod+Return
Open a new terminal (tabbed st).
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+Return
Open a new terminal in the same working directory as the focused window.
.TP
.B Mod+c
Close the focused window.
.TP
.B Mod+space
Cycle to the next layout.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+space
Toggle floating for the focused window.
.TP
.B Mod+b
Toggle the bar.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+q
Quit muhhwm.
.SS Tag navigation
.TP
.B Mod+h
Move to the previous tag in the current namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+l
Move to the next tag in the current namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+j
Move to the previous namespace, keeping position within it.
.TP
.B Mod+k
Move to the next namespace, keeping position within it.
.TP
.B Mod+1\-6
Jump directly to tag N in the current namespace.
.SS Moving windows between tags
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+h
Send the focused window to the previous tag.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+l
Send the focused window to the next tag.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+j
Send the focused window to the previous namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+k
Send the focused window to the next namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+1\-6
Send the focused window to tag N.
.SS Namespace shortcuts
.TP
.B Mod+F1
Switch to the study namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+F2
Switch to the code namespace.
.TP
.B Mod+F3
Switch to the free namespace.
.SS Applications
.TP
.B Mod+e
Open neovim in a terminal.
.TP
.B Mod+n
Open quick notes in neovim.
.TP
.B Mod+Shift+f
Open Firefox.
.SS Menus (Alt key)
.TP
.B Alt+space
dmenu application launcher.
.TP
.B Alt+b
Browser/URL menu.
.TP
.B Alt+f
File manager (lf).
.TP
.B Alt+m
Music menu.
.TP
.B Alt+p
Pomodoro menu.
.TP
.B Alt+Escape
Power menu.
.TP
.B Alt+F10
Network/connection menu.
.TP
.B Alt+Super
All-in-one launcher menu.
.TP
.B Alt+F12
Toggle external display.
.SS Media keys
.TP
.B XF86AudioMute
Toggle master audio mute.
.TP
.B XF86AudioRaiseVolume / XF86AudioLowerVolume
Raise or lower master volume by 1%.
.TP
.B XF86MonBrightnessUp / XF86MonBrightnessDown
Raise or lower screen brightness by 1%.
.TP
.B F4
Toggle microphone capture.
.TP
.B Print
Screenshot menu.
.SH MOUSE
.TP
.B Mod+Button1
Move the window under the cursor.
.TP
.B Mod+Button3
Resize the window under the cursor.
.TP
.B Button1 on tag
View that tag.
.TP
.B Button3 on tag
Toggle that tag into the current view.
.TP
.B Button2 on window title
Zoom (promote) the window to the master area.
.TP
.B Scroll on tag bar (left/right)
Navigate to adjacent tags.
.TP
.B Scroll up on tag bar
Navigate to the previous namespace.
.SH WINDOW RULES
Windows can be assigned to a specific tag and namespace automatically
based on their class, instance, or title. Rules are defined in
.B config.h
before compilation.
